A Security Infrastructure as a Service platform — + CAPABILITIES & INTEGRATIONS An ecosystem of powerful technologies Get the security tools that your business needs An set of capabilities that can be used to automate and manage security operations at Get Started Free Book a demo Leverage open source solutions without the headache . Velociraptor Velociraptor, the endpoint visibility tool, provides the ability to effectively investigate a wide range of digital forensic use It can be used to: Reconstruct attacker activities through digital forensic analysis Hunt for evidence of sophisticated adversaries Investigate malware outbreaks and other suspicious network activities Monitor continuously for suspicious user activities, such as files copied to USB devices Discover whether disclosure of confidential information occurred outside the network Gather endpoint data over time for use in threat hunting and future investigations Velociraptor’s power and flexibility come from the Velociraptor Query Language (VQL). The VQL framework creates highly customized scripts, which can collect, query, and monitor any aspect of an endpoint, groups of endpoints, or an entire Custom VQL scripts are deployed as “Artifacts”. An artifact is a text file written in YAML which encapsulates the VQL, adds descriptions, and provides parameters allowing users to customize the operation of the How it works LimaCharlie makes Velociraptor available as a service that can easily be run on any given endpoint or across the entire This service will automate the deployment and running of Velociraptor It supports three actions: list to show all Artifacts the latest release of Velociraptor supports show to display the usage of a specific Artifact collect to trigger an actual collection of Artifacts Once generated by Velociraptor, a zip file with all collected data is ingested automatically into LimaCharlie where you can download The download from LimaCharlie can also be automated using an Output stream with detection triggers that are fired when it Book A Demo Read the Doc LimaCharlie provides everything a modern cybersecurity system Using their API and "infrastructure as code" approach has empowered us to have access to a robust cybersecurity ecosystem without a substantial amount of upfront Ron CEO , CyberGood Security YARA Scanning LimaCharlie automates management of YARA signature sets and their use in YARA is a tool aimed at (but not limited to) helping malware researchers to identify and classify malware With YARA you can create descriptions of malware families (or whatever you want to describe) based on textual or binary Each description, rule, consists of a set of strings and a boolean expression that determine its How it works The YARA service is designed to help you with all aspects of YARA It takes what is normally a manual piecewise process, provides a framework, and automates Once configured, YARA scans can be run for a particular endpoint or continuously in the background across your entire fleet without impacting The scan is what people generally mean when they say “Yara scanning” - it offers full control but it tends to spike up the memory use, and subsequently impact the On the other hand, continuous scanning (trickle scanning) will have no noticeable impact on the user (target 1% CPU for the feature) but may take longer to To get started with Yara scanning, from the YARA Scanners view available within your organization, pull Yara rules signatures from sources like GitHub Then, configure scanners to scan for matching signatures on Book A Demo Read the Doc We truly feel like LimaCharlie is an extension of our own The tech is great — but the relationship is easily the best Glenn Starkman CEO , Soteria Telemetry Storage Endpoints as well as applications such as AWS, Google Cloud, Office , , Slack, and thousands of others produce vast amounts of The volume of security data is growing, and this growth will continue for the foreseeable This, in turn, leads to several challenges: To detect threats and respond to incidents, it is not sufficient to simply collect all these You need to have the ability to bring them all into one place for correlation and a holistic view of your security To meet the compliance requirements, organizations need to store security data for a set amount of time a solid data storage strategy is also a prerequisite for retroactive threat Data storage is expensive which forces organizations and security teams to sacrifice visibility and trade it for cost To solve these problems, LimaCharlie offers 1 year of full telemetry storage and search capability at no extra How it works Insight is the underlying technology providing storage and search capability for LimaCharlie and is built on top of the Google Cloud With Insight, organizations can - at the click of a button - store and search a year’s worth of data from all of their Using the interface, users can interact with individual endpoints in or search and explore a y

What Is A Financial Advisor? | Zoe Financial Skip to content Main Menu About Zoe Financial Menu Toggle About Us FAQs Join the Zoe Network Financial Planning Menu Toggle Retirement Investing Divorce Tax Strategy Managing Debt Home Purchase Asset Management Windfall Estate Planning Family Planning College Planning Stock Options What Is A Financial Advisor Menu Toggle Advisor Vetting Process How to Find an Advisor How to Interview an Advisor Financial Advisor Fees Resources Menu Toggle The Zoe Blog White Papers Infographics Guides Videos Find An Advisor What Exactly is a Financial Advisor? Therein lies the problem: the title financial advisor is Unfortunately, it is used interchangeably for , fiduciary financial advisors as well as brokers or insurance agents, despite their starkly different roles and This makes it even harder for you to distinguish between great financial advisors – who are true experts and fiduciaries – and salespeople, who are incentivized to and sell products that earn them the highest commissions from banks and large financial Finding The Right Advisor When To Hire An Advisor Things To Consider Finding The Right Advisor Why Is It So Hard to Find a Great Financial Advisor? The financial advisor profession has developed a bad reputation, and for good Although they are all called financial advisors , the majority of them are brokers or insurance salesmen instead of fiduciary advisors… and that As we discussed in Brokers Advisors, brokers and insurance agents are essentially salespeople focused on pushing the most profitable products onto you for their companies’ However, fiduciary advisors are only compensated by you, the This means that the advice they give is objective and If you are unable to differentiate between a salesperson and a advisor , you will have to test their aptitude, knowledge, and That’s because to become an advisor you merely have to pass the Series test, which can be accomplished after about two weeks of study If the advisor’s expertise is adequate, then it’s up to you to figure out whether their expertise aligns with what you and your investments As described in What Makes For a Great Advisor? , the value that consumers are looking for from an advisor has changed dramatically over the last few Back in the day, the value was in their ability to try to “ beat the market ” by picking stocks, bonds, or mutual funds on your Technology and product innovation have commoditized many of those tasks via more passive and investment vehicles, such as index funds or What many consumers want today is a household CFO who looks at their financial life holistically, incorporating risk management, budgeting, taxes, estate planning, and Although many advisors promise this type of service, the reality is that most of their practices are stuck in the past and don’t quite live up to When To Hire An Advisor We’ve listed a few instances in which you should consider hiring an advisor Nearing & Preparing for Retirement This is by far the most common scenario we Transitioning from living off a salary to living off your retirement investments happens only once in your life, so it pays to have a good financial advisor in your There are plenty of decisions to be made, such as: When should I fully retire? Do I have enough saved up to live out the retirement I want? When should I withdraw from my IRA and when should I start withdrawing from Social Security? What is the appropriate mix of bonds, stocks, and cash that I should hold in my portfolio? Which investments should I access first, taking into consideration market conditions and tax implications? A financial advisor can walk you through all of these questions and more, ensuring your financial Newly Single, Legal Separations & Divorce Losing a spouse, through divorce or death, can change everything when it comes to your personal Whether it’s questions regarding property settlements or adjustments in income after a divorce, or death benefits and wills after a death, guidance from a qualified fiduciary advisor who specializes in these circumstances can be very Financial Windfalls Receiving a large sum of money often creates a sense of anxiety as to how to properly manage Be it a business exit, inheritance, personal injury settlements, lottery winnings or life insurance proceeds they all come with big decisions that require proper Starting a Family & Planning for College Getting married or starting a family are big life decisions that raise even bigger questions for your financial situation, such as: How will the budget be handled? How do I align my financial goals and make the appropriate changes to beneficiaries in retirement accounts? When and how do I start planning & savings for my kids college? How do I set up life and disability insurance, write or adjust my will, or adjust my budgets now that I have a newborn? Career Change A promotion, a job change, a partner deciding to stay home to take care of the children, unemployment – all of these car

But why methane from livestock? It turns out that cows and other farm animals have a bit of a burping Through their digestive process, called enteric fermentation, livestock burps cause an astounding 6% of the world’s global That means if cows were a country, they would produce just about as much GHG as the entire European Symbrosia is hard at work developing a breakthrough seaweed supplement that, when sprinkled into animal feed, reduces those methane emissions by over % (Kinley, ). Resources | Orbiit How it works How it works About us About us Resources Resources Try it free Try it free Resources Frequently Asked Questions How do you define an audience? An audience is a group of people who are getting matched in a particular For example, your entire community or company can be a single audience, or you can segment participants into multiple audiences by criteria such as function, seniority or Depending on your chosen plan, you can have multiple audiences, set different cadences, and determine rule sets for For example, a VC fund could have a ‘Heads of Product’ audience and match them on topics, while also connecting the entire portfolio on universal topics of What is the minimum number of people you can form an audience with? Orbiit saves hours of tedious manual work for community managers looking to connect groups of as few as However, the bigger the audience, the more curated the How does the matching process work? Once you set the cadence of the engagement, weekly or monthly virtual chats, the participants who opt in fill in a brief form that informs our matching We match participants based on criteria proven to facilitate strong matches, such as years of experience, function, geography, calendar availability and Can I customize the matching criteria? Depending on your chosen plan, you may be able to customize the matching criteria and add or remove certain Can I preview the matches and change the matches before they go out? Your matching criteria and our algorithm strength eliminate the need for additional time spent on checking We have an average NPS score of across all our engagements to However, for those looking for the ability to perform match customization, this feature will be available for Tier 3 clients in early What is the experience? Do they need to create an account? We understand that platform fatigue is real and your community members are strapped for time, so we purposely chose to steer clear of any logins or cumbersome user profile creation All communication lands directly in their inbox, where they can opt in to an engagement or provide feedback with just a few The only person with a profile and login details is the community manager — or admin — who sets the engagement and reviews the How is the pricing done? Per user? We never want price to be a limiting factor for audience size, so we do not price per There are three tiers to choose from, with increasing Tier 1 is limited to one audience, no client branding, a choice of topics from our existing library, and limited Tier 2 allows for multiple audiences, client branding, robust analytics and Tier 3 is for clients who require customization of matching criteria, topics, branding, account management and detailed What is the minimum contract length? The minimum engagement is six However, there is a % discount for any commitments — the more your community is exposed to the opportunity to connect with one another, the better the interactions and Can I try it for free? Yes, we offer a one month free Get in touch with details about your community using the form at the bottom of this Why is the matching topic based? We believe that every conversation has the potential to be when there is commonality of purpose between We also understand that your community is looking for targeted, meaningful Giving members the opportunity to opt into topics of interest increases satisfaction and Do you come up with the topics, or do I have to? We provide an extensive library of topics, which include suggested icebreakers and talking The library is continuously updated, reflecting the most desirable and trending topics across all In addition, you also have the flexibility to create and customize a topic with the experience of our dedicated client services What is the difference between Orbiit and other online connection platforms? Orbiit is the only platform offering curated connections at Unlike platforms that follow a ‘chat roulette’ model, each Orbiit match ensures a meaningful conversation, strengthened by commonality in topic and profile (such as years of experience, company stage, etc). Orbiit was built with the community manager’s needs in This means you have access to features that enable control of engagements and extraction of valuable feedback, ensuring that the admin’s experience is as smooth as the participant’s. Finally, we cater to communities of all sizes, activating groups with as few as people and as many as a few Want to learn more?
